Form validation
===============

1. Use im-submit="save()" instead of ng-submit. 

im-submit will add a "submitted" boolean to the FormController and css class to the form so we can show the validation errors when the user presses submit.

Use <im-show-error> tags that will also present the server side validation errors.


A simple form tag follows. The name attribute is required:

<form name="contactForm" im-submit="save()" novalidate>

A simple form input with im-show-error (A name attribute is required on the input when using <m-show-error>:

<div class="form-group">
	<label class="col-sm-3 control-label" for="username">{{"Username"| t}}</label>
	<div class="col-sm-9">
		<input type="text" id="username" name="username" class="form-control" ng-model="user.attributes.username" required />
		<im-show-error for="username" im-model="user"></im-show-error>
	</div>
</div>

You can also set custom error messages:

<im-show-error for="passwordConfirm" im-model="user" im-messages="{'imMatch': 'The passwords don\'t match'}"></im-show-error>


